# Architecture

stack: React 19, Vite, TypeScript strict, Tailwind v4
state: SQLite (local-first) via @sqlite.org/sqlite-wasm. no backend unless specified.
  persistence: sqlite-wasm writes to OPFS (Origin Private File System). survives reload.
  fallback: localStorage for ephemeral UI state (theme, sidebar open, etc.) only.
  future: sync layer (e.g. ElectricSQL, cr-sqlite) if multi-device needed. don't abstract yet.
routing: React Router v7. no file-based routing.
data flow: props down, callbacks up. context for db/auth/theme only.

structure:
  src/
    app/          → App.tsx, router, global providers
    pages/        → one file per route
    components/
      ui/         → generic, reusable (Button, Input, Modal)
      features/   → domain-specific (TaskList, SettingsPanel)
    hooks/        → custom hooks only. no business logic in components.
    lib/
      db/
        index.ts  → init sqlite-wasm, export db singleton
        schema.ts → CREATE TABLE statements + migrations
        queries/  → one file per entity (tasks.ts, settings.ts etc.)
      storage.ts  → localStorage wrapper for ephemeral UI state only. typed.
      utils.ts    → pure fns. no side effects.
    types/        → shared TS interfaces. no inline types for shared shapes.

boundaries:
  pages/ → import from components/, hooks/, lib/, types/
  components/ → import from hooks/, lib/, types/ only. never from pages/.
  lib/ → no imports from components/ or pages/.
  hooks/ → import from lib/, types/ only.